<Layout title="About" description="About DevTools Online — free online developer tools, 100% client-side.">
  <h1>About</h1>
  <p>
    <strong>DevTools Online</strong> is a collection of free developer tools
    that run entirely in your browser.
  </p>

  <h2>Why We Built This</h2>
  <p>
    Most "online tools" sites are cluttered with ads, trackers, and dark patterns.
    We wanted something different: <strong>clean, fast, private tools</strong> that
    developers actually enjoy using.
  </p>

  <h2>What Makes Us Different</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>100% Client-Side</strong> — JSON formatting, diff checking, all processing
    happens in your browser. Nothing is ever uploaded to a server.</li>
    <li><strong>No Sign-Up</strong> — Just open a tool and use it. No accounts, no emails, no BS.</li>
    <li><strong>Minimal Ads</strong> — We keep it clean. No pop-ups, no auto-play videos, no
    "one weird trick" banners.</li>
    <li><strong>Minimal & Fast</strong> — No bloated frameworks. Pages load instantly.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Current Tools</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><a href="/json-tools"><strong>JSON Tools</strong></a> — Format, validate, minify, and convert JSON ↔ CSV</li>
    <li><a href="/diff-checker"><strong>Diff Checker</strong></a> — Compare two texts side by side, line by line</li>
  </ul>
  <p>More tools coming soon: Base64, URL encoder, UUID generator, regex tester, and more.</p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>
    Questions, suggestions, or bug reports? Reach out at
    <a href="mailto:hello@YOUR-DOMAIN.com">hello@YOUR-DOMAIN.com</a>.
  </p>
</Layout>
